2 (1951) , 158- 68; idem, Lives and Legends of the Georgian Saints (London 1976)
57- 80. ' '
BSO, II, 804 (E. Gabidzashvili).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract">Peter the Iberian was the son of the king of Georgia. He helped Nestorius preach a homily about the saints. He went on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem and became a monk. He became Bishop of Maiuma in Gaza and was exiled to Egypt in 455.</note>
